br.com.summa.sol.data

Class Duple<X extends Comparable<X>,Y extends Comparable<Y>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • br.com.summa.sol.data.Pair<X,Y>
      • br.com.summa.sol.data.Duple<X,Y>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Duple<X,Y>>

    public class Duple<X extends Comparable<X>,Y extends Comparable<Y>>
extends Pair<X,Y>
implements Comparable<Duple<X,Y>>
    A Comparable Pair. DISCLAIMER: This class is only intended to temporarily store a disjoint pair of objects, for instance when a certain method needs to return two distinct results. However, in cases where these objects make any sense together, it's much better OOP to create a proper custom class to combine them instead.
    Author:
    Einar Saukas
